“Those who don’t believe, when I ascend to the Union Buildings, they are going to collapse.” These were the words of African Content Management (ACM) president Hlaudi Motsoeneng. Motsoeneng was addressing his supporters ahead of the elections on 8 May. What is important in life is believe and I believe i'm the best in South Africa, I believe that God has given me the wisdom to lead South Africa...and those who don’t believe, when I ascend to the Union Buildings they going to collapse," said Hlaudi. 